On Tuesday, April 20, 2004, at 11:37AM, Eron Crites <emcrites(-at-)msn.com> wrote:

>Most tool suppliers have a slotted 1/2 inch drive socket that works just 
>great!  I used to sell S-K tools, and they make a nice one.  I would assume 
>Snap-On and Craftsman would also retail the piece.

If you mean a draglink socket they don't fit but you can put it on the grinder and create the profile for the plug. Whatever chrome you grind off will need to be protected for storage so it doesn't rust.

